description:

- Outstanding potential for redevelopment/subdivision (STCA)
- Scope to bring the existing home back to its former glory
- Single level layout offers excellent indoor to outdoor living
- Multiple outdoor spaces for entertaining, salt water pool
- Chefs' kitchen with large island bench and ample storage
- All bedrooms connect to outdoor spaces, master has ensuite
- Ducted air conditioning, high ceilings, exposed timber beams
- Versatile outbuilding/teenage retreat plus four car spaces
- Close to The King’s School, Tara and James Ruse Selective
- Easily accessible to major arterial roads and Parramatta CBD

Free Building & Pest Report at bw.com.au.

Highlights
* Victorian facade & hedged front entry
* Beautifully preserved period elements
* Separate family living & dining spaces
* Highlight windows, rich natural sunlight
* Large stone kitchen w/ gas cooking
* Opens out to a private timber deck
* Large paved backyard & lush gardens
* Top-floor retreat w/ office/playroom

description:
Ray White Upper North Shore is committed to providing a safe environment for our customers to inspect and buy property and we will be adhering to all government guidelines and restrictions. When attending our open homes, you will be required to check in using the service NSW QR code, wear a mask, practice social distancing and adhere to any instructions given by the agent. Please do not attempt to attend our open homes if you are unwell or have been in contact with a positive COVID case.

Provincial elegance, a substantial and thoughtfully conceived floor plan and an exceptional position combine in this stunning brick residence. The immediate feel is one of coming home with luxury spaces exuding a warm welcome. An absolute highlight is its extraordinary entertaining credentials where sweeping living zones spill out on multiple sides to expansive decks and a stunning covered terrace. The practicalities of life have been considered with the lavish gourmet kitchen positioned to overlook the pool and a private home office custom appointed with an abundance of storage and shelving. This beautiful residence rests on 1265sqm of established gardens and rolling lawns in a picturesque and quiet street across from the greenery of Richmond Park. Every detail confirms the home's ability to accommodate a growing family's needs. Positioned steps to bus services, Gordon East Public School, tennis courts, village shops and rail.

Accommodation Features:
* High ceilings, wide French oak flooring
* Gracious and spacious formal lounge room with gas fireplace
* Sweeping open plan living and dining with open fireplace
* Bi-folds and French doors open to the terraces and deck
* Luxury stone appointed kitchen with immense island bench
* Superb commercial style Falcon gas cooker, bi-fold café window
* Large walk-in pantry, custom appointed home office, ducted a/c
* Lower level full bathroom with access from the external deck and pool
* Five upper level bedrooms with robes, ample storage cupboards
* Master suite with superb ensuite, stylish bathrooms, powder room
* Easy internal access to the over-height double lock up garage

External Features:
* Appealing street presence
* Quiet, adjacent to Richmond Park
* Beautifully established landscaped lawns and gardens
* North facing expansive covered alfresco terrace with skylights
* Natural hard stone paving, spacious deck
* Saltwater pool, rolling lawn for the kids
* Under house cellar and storage area

Location Benefits:
* Across from Richmond Park and tennis courts
* 550m to the 195, 195/6, 196 and 197 bus services to St Ives Chase, Gordon station, Mona Vale and Macquarie University
* 150m to Gordon East Public School
* 1.2km to Gordon station
* 1.3km to Gordon's shops, services and eateries
* Easy access to rail and local private schools

Auction
Saturday 19 February, 1pm
Onsite

Contact
Rowan Lazar 0412 329 789

description:
FIND. Set in one of Balgowlah's most sought-after residential streets and combining glorious Federation character with beautifully renovated interiors, this spacious and light-filled home offers comfortable, easy living flowing over a family-friendly single level.

LOVE. Brimming with heritage charm, this character-rich home has been carefully renovated to maintain its period detail and features high patterned ceilings, original fireplaces, ornate cornices and architraves, as well as picture rails and stunning leadlight feature windows.
- Deluxe new shaker-profile kitchen with Caesarstone centre island, Ilve gas cooking and integrated dishwasher
- Light and spacious open-plan living/dining with a/c, fireplace and bi-fold doors opening onto entertaining deck
- Timber floorboards plus numerous working original fireplaces with ornate surrounds
- Elegant master suite with beautiful fireplace and feature leadlight windows, built-in robes, ceiling fan, ensuite and versatile adjoining sunroom/ dressing room or home office
- Queen-sized second and third bedrooms with built-in robes and plantation shutters
- Sunny entertainer's deck extending onto child-friendly level lawn
- Contemporary bathroom with bath/overhead shower, Caesarstone vanity, and Euro-style laundry
- Off-street parking

LIVE. Within walking distance of Stockland shopping and Balgowlah village, this delightful home enjoys a true lifestyle address close to schools and public transport. This sought-after setting offers easy access to beautiful beaches, reserves and coastal walkways.


RATES/SIZE:
Water rates: Approx $151 pq
Council rates: Approx $366 pq
Size: Approx 285 sqm

ABOUT THE AREA

Local Transport:
- Buses to city CBD, Chatswood, Westfield Warringah Mall and Manly

Shopping:
- Stockland Balgowlah shopping centre and Balgowlah village provide a choice of cafes, shops and restaurants

Schools:
- Manly West Public School
- Balgowlah Boys Campus
- Mackellar Girls Campus

WHAT THE OWNER LOVES:
- The house has a lovely calm and peaceful feeling, and the period features make it such a beautiful, special place to live
- This is a really easy home to live in and the single level is ideal for young children
- We love how close we are to everything – we can walk to dinner or out for coffee and ride our bikes down to Fairlight or Manly for a swim

description:
IMMACULATE SINGLE LEVEL BEACHFRONT CHARMER
DIRECT ACCESS TO CASUARINA BEACH WITH DUAL LIVING OPTION

Here is your opportunity to invest in prime beachfront real estate at entry level pricing. With no neighbour to the south & a park on the beachside, your privacy is assured !!

This custom-built home would suit the home occupier, or is an ideal investment property, with a dual living potential, for extra rental return.

It represents excellent value in our current market. Our beachfront land is very limited & expensive, so buying an established home makes great investment sense.

Situated in dress circle Collins Lane, on a 16-metre-wide block, this gorgeous, single level home is a rare find.

Cleverly designed for multi-generational living, the 2-bedroom granny flat option includes a self-contained living area, bathroom and kitchenette, for extended family or friends to be accommodated with ease.

Alternatively, the 4 bedroom home has room for a pool and will accommodate a family, or retired couple as required. The 4th bedroom has separate access to the front of the home & would also be ideal for home office use.

With lush parklands surrounding the home and direct beach access from your back gate, you will love this low maintenance, quality beachfront home, where you have time to enjoy our local cafes and highly appointed restaurants.

Relax to the sound of the waves gently breaking on pristine Casuarina Beach at your doorstep.

COTTAGE STYLE CHARM IN PRIME BEACHFRONT LOCATION

The generous master bedroom opens to a private deck, surrounded by mature gardens and is drenched in sunshine, the perfect spot for your morning cuppa !!!

A very sleek ensuite boasts floor to ceiling tiling, his and hers vanities and a dumper shower to warm up in after your daily surf.

There is ample storage for all your designer clothing and personal items everywhere throughout this entire home.

Entertaining is a dream in the very modern kitchen with Artusi appliances, induction cooktop, steam oven, dishwasher, Caesar stone island benchtop and custom-built cabinetry.

The kitchenette option allows guests or teenagers to cater for themselves. Doesn't that sound like a great idea !!!

A north facing deck, as well as a huge beachside deck means you can entertain in all weather conditions.

CONTACT NICK WITHERIFF on 0405 618 477 TO ARRANGE YOUR PRIVATE VIEWING TODAY


PROPERTY FEATURES:
- 4 good sized bedrooms
- 3 sleek bathrooms
- 2nd laundry & kitchenette option
- Additional study space
- 2nd living room
- 2 outdoor entertaining decks
- Ceiling fans throughout
- 3-metre-high ceilings
- Plantation shutters
- Fully fenced yard with mature gardens
- Alarm set to 2 sections of the home
- Insulated walls and ceilings
- Crimesh Screens
- Ultra colorbond roofing and gutters
- Double garage with extra space for the surfboards
- Granny flat or home office option with separate access
- Permanent rental return (approx.) $1,400 - $1,500 per week
- Holiday returns (approx.) Peak $9,000 - $10,000 per week
- Easter $7,500 - $8,000 per week
- Holidays $5,000 per week
- Off Season $2,500 - $3,000 per week

5 MINUTES TO NEW TWEED VALLEY HOSPITAL (under construction)
15 MINUTES TO GOLD COAST AIRPORT
30 MINUTES TO BYRON BAY
CLOSE TO CAFES, SHOPS, RESTAURANTS, COLES SHOPPING CENTRE, MEDICAL, CHILD CARE, CASUARINA REC CENTRE.

description:
This 6m wide cottage is quintessential Paddington living with all the charm of its 1830s vintage. In a mews-like enclave just behind The Intersection's fashion hub, the two-storey cottage features the bonus of a loft-style studio at the rear with its own private entry and access via Mary Place to secure parking a rare bonus in the heart of the village. Entertain alfresco on the private deck or step outside and explore a world of arts, fashion and entertainment, 100m to institutions like Acne Studios, Mecca and Scanlan & Theodore. Ready for its next make over the last renovation was by Sulman Award winning architect, Vivian Fraser that makes the most of its sunny disposition.
- 1830s cottage with a 6m frontage
- Cul-de-sac with no through traffic
- Historic charm, village convenience
- Short stroll to five ways
- Warm hardwood floors, exposed brick
- Main with built-ins and Kauri boards
- Loads of natural light and fresh air
- Living room with a Jetmaster fireplace
- Stainless steel kitchen and open dining
- Smeg gas cooker, Bosch dishwasher
- Study/home office opens outdoors
- Entertainer's deck framed by palms
- Quiet privacy, an oasis in the city
- Stylish bathroom with stone finishes
- Internal laundry, gas heating bayonet
- Reverse air and plantation shutters
- Auto secure parking via Mary Place

Please note when attending open for inspections we kindly ask that you adhere to the current COVID safety guidelines.

Deceptively spacious and featuring quality inclusions throughout, the ocean views highlight the coastal delights that await close by. It's quiet-street location is an easy walk to Randwick Village shops, Cafes, Coogee Beach and Fred Hollows Reserve. This beautiful appointed home will appeal to downsizers and growing families alike, particularly those looking for that third bedroom space as well as following functioning Home Office environment

• Zoned living areas with original Jarrah hardwood floors and sky light
• Cook's kitchen with Blanco gas cooker & stone benches
• King-size master Master Bedroom. Large adjoining Sunroom provides a with fully functional work-from-home office setup & ocean views
• Double size 2nd bedroom. The flexible 3rd Bedroom space is separately accessible either externally or internally via bedroom 2 and offers many usage options. Currently configured as a Nursery

description:
The picturesque façade of this timeless residence welcomes you inside to an exquisite blend of period charm and contemporary living. High ceilings, stunning stonework and timber beams frame the hall leading to the rear extension. Continuing the wow factor is the resort-style bathroom with feature stonework. The master bedroom boasts an ensuite and walk-in robe while all four bedrooms are equipped with ceiling fans. A true entertainer's delight featuring an island kitchen with gas stovetop connecting to an air-conditioned open plan dining and living zone. description:
Soak It Up On Sunpatch
Located on one of the most popular and beloved streets the South Coast has to offer, this homage to the sleepy seaside holiday town of yesteryear is just 600m to the golden sands of Tomakin Cove and 800m to Barlings Beach.

Beautifully kept, neat and tidy with everything you need in a comfortable holiday home or intelligent investment, 76 Sunpatch Parade represents the very best of the sleepy coastal lifestyle you've been dreaming about.

Featuring 3 bedrooms, one bathroom, two toilets and kitchen with walk-in pantry and spacious living room, this property is loaded with potential, offering the opportunity to move in now, holiday let or rent out while you make plans for the future.

A large 730 square metre block offers a well kept front yard and an expansive backyard with garage and fenced backyard.

This home is the perfect opportunity to enter the market in a highly sought after location directly across the road from the river which provides easy access for fishing and kayaking and close to beaches, Tomago River, schools, shops and so much more.

The possibilities at 76 Sunpatch Parade are many and the drawbacks are few. Find out how you can make this little slice of South Coast Paradise your own.

Pest and Building Reports also available.

No Offers Accepted Prior
In Room & Online Auction Saturday 19th February

description:
Welcome home to this expansive and grand family residence. Architecturally designed to create the ultimate entertainers haven, this stunning waterfront home captures breathtaking uninterrupted views from every seat in the house. The spacious layout, high ceilings, copious boating facilities and indoor lap pool showcase the exemplar luxurious family lifestyle on offer.

With a multitude of bedrooms, generous 1,266sqm block and a tightly held street address, this home offers a family of any size, a warm & tranquil place to retreat to or a charismatic event space ready to entertain groups of any size at any moment.

Splash around in the indoor swimming pool, a perfect fit for either hotter summer days or cooler weather. Soak in the sunlight as you relax on one of the multiple decks and balconies in this light filled residence. Savor the scenery by starting your days on the terrace or by the boat shed.

Take your boat out for a joyride and enjoy your weekends down at the boat house located by the waters edge. Slip rails, electric winch, jetty, ocean pool and boat storage are all on offer for the avid boatsmen. All boating facilities are on title and no Permissive occupancy fees apply. Your perfect getaway can be fulfilled as the boat house is constructed with a bedroom with a built-in robe, en-suite, study and kitchen. Start a captivating lifestyle with this intriguing property where you and your family can enjoy the greenery and stunning water views. An unparalleled opportunity you would not want to miss out on!

Contact Jack Huggett of Realm Property Group for further information on 0422 690 929

description:
This stunning acreage property is set on 2.7 acres and is tucked away in Glenning Valley's most prestigious pocket of lifestyle homes, and it will without a doubt have you falling in love. Only 4 years young and custom built, it is unrivaled with its high set aspect, a superb and well thought out design and boasting a entertaining area that will have all of your friends and family coming back for more.

The main features include

• 5 generous sized bedrooms with built in wardrobes to 4 rooms and walk in robe to the master bedroom
• 2 bathrooms with ensuite to the master bedroom
• 3rd toilet/powder room
• Double garage with internal access plus a second detached double garage
• The whole block is fully fenced and gated making it completely secure for dogs and animals
• Living areas comprise a huge open plan lounge/family/dining room with soaring pitched roof ceiling that extends effortlessly through to the outdoor decking area. The kids will absolutely love the seperate media room that is perfect for movie nights
• The kitchen is gorgeous with quality fixtures and fittings, breakfast bar and it overlooks the outdoor area and the open plan living, plus there is a butlers pantry
• In the middle of the open plan living room you have a stone fireplace that is one of the homes standout features. Absolutely spectacular!
• As you step outside to the huge decking area and take in the lovely view you'll find two towering stone pylons, glass balustrades and a wide travertine staircase that takes you down to the sensational in ground pool surrounded in travertine pavers
• A awesome cabana area compliments the pool and it features lighting, speakers and a tv that drops down from the ceiling
• A stunning firepit and hard wood timber sitting area
• Out the back of the home you're welcomed by another undercover decking area for entertaining that overlooks the landscaped gardens and water feature plus there is a outdoor shower
• A recently installed dam
• The home is steel frame construction
• Gorgeous timber floors throughout the living areas
• Ducted air throughout
• Solar powered
• Sonos speaker sound system that runs throughout the living areas and outdoor entertaining areas

This standout example of grandeur acreage living is unmatched in the area and has to be seen to appreciate what has been created here. Located within a short 5-10 drive to all amenities including Shelly Beach, shops and schools plus only a 15 minute drive to the M1. This is one opportunity not to be missed

description:
Situated on a private, high-set 2,630sqm parcel in a residential location with spectacular valley views, this property has undergone a complete transformation inside and out, offering future owners the opportunity to simply move in and unpack.

With quality appointments, the interiors are spacious and offer a beautiful garden outlook from every window. The living areas are open plan and flow seamlessly to the outdoor living spaces. The brand-new kitchen features 40mm stone tops and matched, dark, brushed stainless appliances incorporating the latest technologies.

All bedrooms have built-in robes, the master having a large walk-in robe plus an ensuite. In addition, the fifth bedroom also has an ensuite and study nook. The study could be converted to a sixth bedroom if required.

The sunsets are incredible and there are many spots from which they can be enjoyed. Outdoor entertaining and relaxing are a breeze with a rear open pergola and grassed garden setting, plus a covered alfresco setting overlooking the freeform swimming pool at the front of the home. The property has been well designed with connecting pathways, garden lighting and irrigation.

Extensive parking areas have been created making the most of the land size. Several cars can be parked on the concrete areas to the front of the home and a stone pebble parking area below the pool area will easily accommodate several vehicles, a caravan or boat. This will appeal to those with lots of 'toys' or a tradesperson with multiple vehicles.

The property is a very short (2km) drive from Avoca Beach and town centre, there is a bus stop within a few metres, and main shopping centres and public and private schools are within easy reach.

For a detailed eBook including a list of all recent improvements, please email the agent. You will receive an immediate response. (If you don't receive a speedy reply perhaps check your junk mail)

description:
"Numeralla" offers the opportunity to buy a productive 2,200 acre property that has been in the same family for 4 generations. It has been well-managed, with consistent fertiliser history, sound weed control and fencing. The landform is mostly undulating to a little steep in places and soils are mostly grey/pinkish loams and granite. Approximately 60% of "Numeralla" has been cleared, except for shade and shelter, with the remaining 40% timbered mostly with Yellow Box, White Box, Stringy Bark and Kurrajong. Water is a feature of the property, with about 4 kilometres of frontage to the permanent Green Valley Creek, double frontage to Pools Gully Creek, 20 dams, an old well. A very reliable hole in the creek is equipped with submersible mains' power pump, that lifts water to a header tank and there is good roof-water storage connected to the house.
The Sallys Flat area is highly regarded as fine wool-growing region, having produced numerous "Golden Bale" award winners over many decades. "Numeralla" has been consistently producing good quality 17 micron wool for many years, as well as mostly Shorthorn cattle.

Some of the many features of "Numeralla" include:
• Four Bedroom Homestead (including a sleep-out)
• Approximately 150m2 machinery shed, with concrete floor. The old shearing shed has been stripped out to create a machinery shed, which doubles as under-cover shedding at shearing time and has sheep yards attached.
• 3 stand shearing shed, with yards and loading ramp attached
• Timber cattle yards
• Hay shed
• Mobile coverage, land line and satelite NBN
• Two-bedroom cottage, ideal for additional income from holiday-makers or hunters
• Small hut near the main homestead, suitable children's sleep-over etc
• Fenced into about 30 well-designed paddocks, with sound vehicular access, via good tracks

"Numeralla" represents an opportunity to purchase a well-located property, with enough scale to sustain a family, although, being only 55 minutes' drive, is within commuting distance to Bathurst. 1 hour to Mudgee and 3hr 45min to Sydney. It's location lends itself to farm-stay, hunting and 4x4 camping holidays for extra income.
The property has bitumen-sealed frontage to Hill End Road but the homestead is set about 4.3 kilometres of all-weather gravel road from the bitumen.

The owners of "Numeralla" are committed to selling and are offering the property For Sale at Auction, unless sold prior to the event. . Your inspection is highly recommended.

Three bedrooms with built in wardrobes and 2 bathrooms are also situated on this level and include the main bedroom with ensuite and north facing separate balcony to bring in the sea breeze and sunlight.

description:
Once you step foot inside this home, you'll be amazed by the great sense of size and space. On the downstairs level, you have generous living spaces that connect very well with the outdoor entertaining area and rear yard. The country style kitchen, dining, and lounge area with timber floors and a beautiful open fireplace, are all set on this level. Other features of this level include a bathroom with separate toilet, renovated laundry, internal access to the single car garage and last but not least, the original main bedroom which is currently being utilised as an extra living space but could be a great office for those working from home.

Upstairs, you will find another spacious living room with five adjoining bedrooms. Each bedroom features built in wardrobes and the master enjoys a walk in robe and ensuite. The living area and some bedrooms enjoy a mountain outlook. Additionally, there's a bathroom with separate toilet, a linen cupboard and ample storage space.

Outside, the north facing backyard, provides plenty of room for kids and pets to run around and play. This home is ideally positioned within a short walking distance to the local supermarket, town centre, sporting ovals, parks and schools. Jump in your car and be at Werri or Seven Mile Beach in just minutes!

description:
The Hamptons style is defined by cool, classic and sophisticated designs that meet rustic, casual beach vibes. Substitute beach for mountains and welcome home!

This master designed and built family home sits proudly on the high side of Box Hill's newest estate, Hillsbrook. Meticulously designed and built by master custom builder Quinn Homes, their more than 40 years experience emanates throughout this family home. The entry greets you with a light and airy void, through to the open plan kitchen, living and dining. They say the kitchen is the heart of the home and this one will not disappoint! Shaker style cabinets with 40mm Calacutta marble inspired Casesarstone benchtops are all beautifully framed by the full width feature window splashback; stainless steel Smeg appliances and gas cooking ensures the chef of the family is well catered for. The oversized laundry sits off the kitchen and includes plenty of storage cupboards as well as overheard shelving and indoor hanging rail.

The formal loungeroom is tucked away from the main living spaces, perfect for those long winter nights and summer days relaxing in front of the tv, or entertaining with friends and family. Upstairs hosts 3 extra large bedrooms with built in robes serviced by the main bathroom with a large freestanding bathtub; and a rumpus/living area for the kids.

The master suite exudes indulgence with feature recessed bed nook, overhead reading lights and highlite window. His and her walk in robes leading to the ensuite , double bowl vanity, pigeon pair mirrors and a spacious semi frameless shower with feature tiled niche make this space one you will be happy to wake up to. Relax and unwind after a long day, sipping champagne and enjoying the mountain views and sunset on your private balcony.

description:
Welcome to No. 16 - Tucked away in a peaceful location in a highly sought after pocket of Narara, this picture perfect home sets the scene for a great family lifestyle. Offering sleek, light filled freshly painted interiors, a spacious and versatile floorplan with a dream outdoor alfresco entertaining area – all the boxes have been ticked. A welcoming tiled entryway leads into a stylish and comfortable interior graced with an abundance of natural light and complemented by quality finishes and plenty of room to entertain.

The easy flowing open floorplan offering you choice of multiple living and dining areas deliver plenty of space for the whole family. Entertain out the back under the ultimate in alfresco covered entertaining area with your very own built-in pizza oven/bbq combo, all overlooking the lush lawn/advanced landscaped private and fully fenced yard. Set in this sought after tree lined street, just a few doors from natural parklands and a brilliant playground for the kids & just a short walk to the very popular St Philips Christian School. This one is a must to see!

Features include:
- Beautifully presented single level residence nestled away in a peaceful locale
- Privately positioned in a tree lined street with a lush leafy outlook
- Immaculate brick and tile exterior, embraced by landscaped grounds and gardens
- Master suite complete with renovated ensuite offering floor to ceiling tiles & wall hung vanity + Built-in robe & ceiling fan
- Three additional generously sized bedrooms (all with built in robes)
- Modern kitchen with crisp white cabinetry, stainless steel appliances, ample storage and inviting breakfast bar – all looking out across the outdoor entertaining zone
- Multiple formal and informal living areas + cosy slow combustion fire place & offering plenty of space for the whole family
- Brilliant outdoor sanctuary – the ultimate covered alfresco entertaining area with built-in pizza oven/bbq offering the best in outdoor living surrounded by advanced landscaped gardens and lush green lawn all fenced & private, setting the scene for family and friends to gather and enjoy all year round. Perfect for the kids and pets to play.
- Fresh natural light 3-way main bathroom complete with separate bath shower and toilet.
- Parking is a breeze with single lock up garage – (the practical workshop option incl 3 phase power + great storage) plus double high set oversized carport – perfect for the caravan/boat work vans etc & then there the addition of extra off street parking with the U shaped driveway– just so many options

Extras include: ducted air conditioning, ceiling fans, slow combustion fire place, natural gas bayonet inside and out, gas hot water, garden shed, water tank & pump, LED lighting & freshly painted throughout, 22 x solar panels & NBN direct to the home

All set in an incredibly convenient location offering easy access to local schools, bus & train, Gosford CBD, waterfront, cafes & hospitals. For the commuters the M1 for access to Sydney & Newcastle along with the University of Newcastle (Ourimbah Campus) Westfield Tuggerah, Erina Fair, all within 15 minutes. Adding to all of this is a selection of beautiful beaches & bushwalks are all within 20 minutes. If you've been searching for your dream home in Narara - this property is an absolute must see.
For any further questions or to arrange an inspection call Jodie Walsh today on 0424 914364

description:
Charming home with Moore than meets the eye

BED 4 | BATH 2 | LIVING 2 | CAR 1

One for the history buffs, this is a sensational opportunity to be part of local lore with what is believed to be the footings of Charles Moore's 'Moorecourt' in your backyard. If this isn't enough to pique your interest, then perhaps being on a near-level block only two minutes to town, schools, and walking distance to the train station is what you're looking for.

Greet each morning with natural light filling the open spaces and high ceilings of the lounge and dining areas. The galley-style kitchen with natural gas cooking and walk-in pantry easily hosts the home, while providing smooth access to the outdoor entertaining area. Four carpeted bedrooms fit the family, with two on each level and all fitted with built-in wardrobes, while you enjoy the instantaneous gas hot water in the ensuite with double shower, or the oversized family bathroom with built-in bath and huge skylight. A study nook or second living area extends the flexibility of the home, along with the external studio offering two spaces ideal for a rumpus or home office.

To the rear of the home, the deep and fully covered veranda overlooks the level yard, boasting an established garden with fully fenced security, the tools are comfortably stored in the two garden sheds plus a third potting shed, and the carport provides excellent side access. Additional features to note include multiple split-system air conditioning units, gas bayonet to the lounge, internal laundry, great roof storage and access.

Summary of features
• Near-level block only two minutes to town, schools, and walking distance to the train station, with local history on your doorstep
• Large windows to the spacious lounge and dining area; galley-style kitchen with natural gas cooking and walk-in pantry,
• Four carpeted bedrooms all with built-in wardrobes, instantaneous gas hot water in the ensuite with double shower and oversized family bathroom with built-in bath and huge skylight,
• Study nook or second living area, external studio offering two spaces ideal for a rumpus or home office, two garden sheds plus a third potting shed,
• Covered entertaining area overlooks the established garden with fully fenced security, and the carport provides excellent side access.

Please contact Lister Estate Agents – Springwood to book your private inspection of this charming home in a supreme location.

description:
There is absolutely no doubt, that the flavour of the last 2 years has been extra space and more privacy. Whether its space to relax, space from neighbours or just some rolling green land to appease the nervous system, it’s where value is found.

As towns start to join and the population increases, the riverside village of Lawrence has become, a funky little hot spot. There is no need to despair, this property package is off the main road and tucked away at the end of its own little cul-de-sac.

Here, you have a very generous 1-acre allotment (approx. 4046m2). As you are the second last house on this quiet no-through street, your views and aspect are literally expansive green paddocks. Enough room for all your pursuits, the yard is fully fenced and pet-proof.

Boats, caravans, vehicles, teenagers and/or the home-based business are catered for here! The 17.5 x 8.5m colorbond shed with 3-metre-high roller doors is absolutely outstanding with its 4 bays plus a separate partitioned workshop area. Here there is a separate bathroom with shower, vanity, storage, and loo. The workshop area boasts a 3.5m work bench, power, and lighting. The 3kw solar system and large poly water tank attached to the shed a clear bonus. If that doesn’t quite cut-it (as if it wouldn’t) we have two shipping containers for ‘extra’ storage with a dome cover for the caravan or boat.

The house is light filled, has been well maintained and recently refurbished. As you enter the house, you are immediately impressed by the polished timber floors that give warmth to the open plan design of living, dining, and grazing (the kitchen is looking awesome with its recent face-lift).

The living area provides a combustion heater to warm the house in Winter and there are fans for the warmer days. This area leads out to the full-length verandah. All three bedrooms are carpeted, have BIR's and the main offers an ensuite for convenience. The main bathroom is a great all-rounder as it is fully equipped.

The extra-large renovated laundry is a feature of the home with modern styling, generous storage space and direct access onto the large covered front deck. The outside area is perfect for relaxing or entertaining friends and family. This is a great and functional space and leads directly to the undercover carport. In addition, there is a freestanding 6 x 3m pergola for more entertaining options, a garden shed and small woodshed.

All this within just a few km to Clarence River (with boat ramp and jetty), the Lawrence Convenience Store (with fuel, groceries and bottle shop) and the Lawrence Tavern (with a great reputation for meals and friendly atmosphere). The townships of Maclean and Grafton are within a 20-30 minute drive, plus the pristine coastal beaches of Yamba and Brooms Head are only 40 minutes away.

First home, last home, work/life station, home base for when you are travelling - whatever stage of life you are in there is a very good chance this property package is a great match. Contact Kylie Swift on 0488 161 621

description:
Looking to seriously step up on your style of living? Call our office today to inspect this beautifully presented family home located in one of Wingham's most preferred neighbourhoods.
Sitting proudly on a generous 853 sq metre corner block this property affords a mile of space for the growing family who is looking to enjoy a modern home with all the trimmings of a lux lifestyle.
Why on earth would you consider buying a block and building a new home when you can secure a home like this and simply move in, unpack your boxes, and put your feet up from day one?
Features:-
* Low maintenance brick and tiled roof construction with established gardens and landscaping.
* Spacious modern interior with fresh floor coverings and paintwork throughout.
* Stunning modern kitchen boasts an island bench, dishwasher, 900mm wide oven/cooktop, pendant lighting & quality Caesarstone benchtops.
* Freshly renovated bathroom is a showpiece in itself! Free standing bath, large shower, quality fixtures & fittings.
* Three large bedrooms. Master boasts air conditioning, fan and a giant walk in robe. Bedrooms two and three also have built in robes and fans.
* Open plan main living room adjoins the kitchen. Air conditioning and a ceiling fan ensure year-round comfort here.
* Generous second living room offers space for a dining setting and a larger loungeroom furniture. Air conditioning, plenty of windows and a recessed wall niche for a large television top off an attractive area of the property.
* Fully covered outdoor BBQ / entertaining area overlooks the inviting in ground saltwater pool.
* Well fenced fully landscaped rear yard and a double size garden shed for extra storage space.
* Oversized single car garage with auto roller door opener and internal access to the home.
* Side gateway allows for yard access if storage of a boat, trailer or caravan is needed behind a fence line.
* Elevated position allows for the cooling north easterly summer breezes to flow through the home.
* Situated just a short drive from a choice of schools, shopping centre and Wingham Golf Club.

Do the math and discover that this modern home offers exceptional value for money when compared to the cost and timeline of building a new property. You know the market is hot and you know that properties are hard to come so inspect 10 Sunset Avenue as soon as you possibly can.

description:
Perched high on the ridge overlooking Queens Park, this sun-filled family home holds a prized parkfront setting with a 6m setback delivering a superb sense of peace and privacy. Channelling the relaxed vibe of the Amalfi Coast, the two storey home is wrapped in lush tropical gardens with a sequence of outdoor spaces for relaxing or entertaining in the sunshine. Facing north with views over the park from both levels, the 7m wide semi is freestanding to the east and embraces the outdoors with bright and breezy living spaces and a skylit island kitchen leading out to a Blackbutt deck and garden cabana. A pared back aesthetic with shades of white evokes a sense of calm enhanced by tranquil leafy outlooks with a study or playroom and scope to extend the upper level in the future (STCA). With the park as your playground, the three-bedroom home is footsteps to Shed Cafe and an easy walk to Centennial Park making it ideal for the active family with close proximity to a choice of beaches and schools.

* Private setting opposite Queens Park
* Sunny NE aspect, 7m wide frontage
* Deep setback with off street parking
* Sweeping views over the park grounds
* Wide entry hall, whitewashed boards
* 3 double bedrooms, 2 with built-ins
* Study/retreat with a Velux sky window
* Spacious dining, classic high ceilings
* Open plan living with a leafy outlook
* Family friendly Caesarstone kitchen
* Smeg gas cooker, Bosch dishwasher
* Breakfast bar/casual dining, reverse air
* Blackbutt deck and established gardens
* Garden cabana, workshop/store shed
* Fresh white bathroom with a bathtub
* Separate laundry with an extra W.C.
* Sandstone foundations, cellar storage
* Attic storage and Velux sky windows
* Outdoor lighting, magical by night
* Potential to further extend STCA
* 300m stroll to St Catherine's School
* Walk across the park to Bondi Junction
* Close to Bronte and Clovelly Beaches

description:
Fall in love with this stunning absolute beachfront two-storey penthouse.
Watch the sunrise over the Pacific Ocean and wonderful sunsets over Lake Tuggerah.

Designed for sophisticated coastal living, this exceptional apartment is located within the sought-after Nautilus Building, showcasing high-end finishes throughout.

The complex itself has been built by an award-winning Master Builder.
Marble Travertine floors throughout, including all bathrooms and terraces, Miele appliances, Caesarstone benchtops, fully ducted air-conditioning, video intercom, back-to-base alarm, lift access from the car park to the apartment and camera surveillance security in the underground carpark.

The apartment is of exceptional proportions for an absolute beachfront, boasting;

- 482 sqm on title
- 243 sqm of internal space
- 158 sqm over four terraces
- 18 sqm of planter boxes
- 63 sqm of underground security parking for four cars

The outstanding position, enormous proportions, and quality finishes throughout make this home a very rare and desirable offering.
(All sqm measurements are according to the approved Strata Plan)

11/9-13 Hutton Road, The Entrance North offers a luxurious beachfront lifestyle, and amenities nearby including:

- A wide choice of excellent restaurants right along the coastal strip
- The wonderful bicycle track around Lake Tuggerah is 200 metres from the
Nautilus complex
- To the north is the Magenta Shores Golf & Country Club; the only private
golf course located on the Central Coast - and the surfing mecca of
Soldier's Beach.

To the south are many more pristine beaches: The Entrance Beach, Ocean Baths, Blue Bay and Toowoon Bay. The family-friendly seaside township of The Entrance, Lakeside Shopping Centre, the vibrant & eclectic Long Jetty shopping strip, Bateau Bay Village, Erina Fair and Westfield Tuggerah Shopping Centres include all major retailers and numerous specialty shops.

- The International Crowne Plaza Terrigal Pacific Hotel is only a short drive
south.
- The Mingara Recreation Club, Tuggerah train station and M1 Motorway are all
within 15 minutes drive from the apartment. Front door to Sydney CBD is
approx. 1h 30 min and to Newcastle CBD approx. 1h 10 min.

PARTICULARS

description:
Joel Simpson from Ray White Castle Hill proudly presents to the market 34 Lockhart Avenue, Castle Hill for public auction at the Castle Hill RSL 7:00pm Luxe Room 23rd of February.

Are you tired of looking at properties that are all the same? This large and unique family home offers something a bit different and is a must see on your property inspection list.

Situated on the high side of the street on an impressive, level 930m² parcel of blue-chip land in the highly sought-after and prestigious New England Estate, 34 Lockhart Avenue provides easy access to public transport including the City bus and is only minutes' walk to the new Sydney Metro rail. Within close proximity is the Castle Towers shopping precinct, Samuel Gilbert, Castle Hill High School, Fred Catterson recreational sporting complex and Heritage Park.

This Architecturally designed 8 year old family home ticks the boxes as a relaxed family home and an entertainer's haven. Spread over a thoughtful single level design, the home offers multiple living zones including a theatre room perfect for family movie nights. stone benchtops frame the gourmet kitchen which includes a double oven, induction cooktop and a over sized walk in pantry. A servery window opens from the kitchen onto your private alfresco.
The master suite, nursery/study is set away from the other bedrooms for peace and quiet, and features a walk-in wardrobe as well as an ensuite. Clever design sets the other three bedrooms and home office away from the main living zones, with a contemporary bathroom featuring modern tiles and a bathtub positioned in the same wing.

Featuring:
* Five bedrooms plus study/parents retreat/nursery or optional fifth bedroom all with built in robes
* Home office or 6th bedroom option
* Master bedroom with walk-in robe and ensuite
* Gourmet kitchen and stainless steel appliances, stone benchtops and Breakfast bar
* Three zoned Ducted Air conditioning
* Media or games room
* Double car garage with ample storage
* Automated roller shutters to the garage
* High Ceilings throughout
* Home alarm

Location features:
* Walk to Castle Towers
* Walk to Castle Hill Train Station
* Walk to Samuel Gilbert, Castle Hill High & Oakhill College
* Walk to Major and local bus

To truly appreciate all this property has to offer, call Joel Simpson today on 0450 907 598 to book an inspection. The owners are committed to achieving a result and have given instructions that the home WILL BE SOLD!

description:
Loved for the last 40 years is this charming family home nestled on a rectangular 974 sqm of manicured land. With near level access from the street, you are greeted by a picturesque English Garden which will surely impress as you are led over sandstone to your reception. The single level accommodation has a natural flow as one wing leads to your bedrooms and the other to your living area with an eat-in Kitchen at its heart. There are three well-proportioned bedrooms with tranquil aspects, centered around a family bathroom and a separate W.C. The other wing comprises a formal/informal lounge/dining area with dual aspect and beautiful vistas flowing seamlessly to the covered entertaining deck. There is an additional teenage/in-laws retreat on the lower level with separate access.
The landscaped gardens have been meticulously cultivated over the current owner's tenure with the purchaser reaping the rewards of their achievement. Child-friendly lawns now offer outdoor options aplenty where one can retreat and play. A built-in BBQ greets you poolside with a shady dining patio complementing this space. A separate complete bathroom is also located on the Pool level. The lock up garage has a high clearance for storage with plenty of additional storage around the house.

The home is located within close proximity to Gordon's transport and shopping precinct, St Ives Shopping Centre and surrounded by excellent public and private schools.
This unique opportunity normally comes once in a generation, so come and inspect.

Property Highlights:
•974sqm block of land offering sweeping panoramic views from the backyard.
•Three bedrooms with beautiful, bright and leafy outlook, two with built-in robes.
•Bathroom with shower over bath (great for small kids and infants).
•Formal/Informal combined living and dining rooms featuring a bay window.
•Alfresco covered entertaining deck with sweeping views over Degotardi Park.
•Sun-drenched elegant eat-in kitchen with breakfast area and pantry.
•Multiple outdoor entertaining spaces including bespoke outdoor BBQ, level lawns, an entertaining terrace and a resort style pool.
•In-law's/Teenager's retreat and additional bathroom including a Laundry
•Lock up garage with ample space for storage and an internal access.
•450 metre walk to Gordon East Primary School and Killara High School catchment
•1.5km to Gordon's train station and shopping. 7km to Chatswood and 20km to Sydney's CBD.

description: This is coastal living at its best. Walk out your back gate, across the grass to the beach and feel like you are on holidays every day. The golden sands of Werri Beach are literally 250m away and you can hear the waves calling you over, to go for a swim or surf! Maybe you will just grab a coffee and start the day a little slower by heading out to your sun-drenched deck to survey the swell first. This beachside location has it all, so close to the patrolled beach end of the beach and rockpool, yet still close to the Gerringong township to meet friends at the cafes or the Hill Bar. Features include timber floorboards, ocean views from the main bedroom and living areas, open plan living, robes for all bedrooms and a huge entertaining deck. Out the back, a brand-new pool awaits, along with a huge undercover area with great storage, plus a toilet and shower for when you arrive home from the beach. Quiet culdesac location and the spacious backyard is complemented by the reserve over the back fence, ideal for a game of cricket. If you're looking for a perfectly positioned weekender or somewhere to settle down, this might be the one.

description:
If you are attracted to a manageable hobby farm acreage of around 10 acres with an immaculately kept six bedroom homestead, you've found it!
Ideally located in sought after Wallaroo with sealed road frontage just 5 mins drive to Hall and 30 mins to Canberra CBD, this property is ideal for those families wanting an easy rural lifestyle.

The single level homestead with full wrap around verandah is full of character with tasteful use of natural timbers and feature sandstock bricks. It has been lovingly maintained and is beautifully presented offering five bedrooms plus study, a huge open plan living area adjacent to the updated kitchen, all overlooking the spectacular gardens and surrounding countryside.

The easy care grounds surrounding the home are well designed with a mix of gardens and open green space with well established mature trees. Beyond the house paddock there are four well fenced paddocks with quality pasture providing enough space for a couple of horses, large pets or perhaps for some horticultural uses. Water won't be a problem here - In addition to the three rainwater tanks supplying the house, studio and shed - two dams provide for gardens and animals plus there is a registered bore which you could bring into operation to utilise for stock and domestic use.

A hobby farm is not complete without good shedding, so you will appreciate the large high roof 9m X 10m shed with workshop space, concrete floor, power and 3 roller doors. Adjoining the shed there is a two story studio which is newly lined and currently furnished with double beds in two rooms, kitchenette, bathroom, living room, sitting room, slow combustion fireplace and air conditioning, approx 80m2 (the shed and studio are approved as shed only).

If dreaming of a country lifestyle whilst working in Canberra, do not miss the opportunity to view this property.

Contact Mark Johnstone on 0414 382 093 for enquiries or come along to our next open exhibition.

PLEASE NOTE THIS PROPERTY WILL GO TO AUCTION ON THURSDAY 17TH FEBRUARY, AT 2/14 WALES ST BELCONNEN

description:

description:
Secreted behind the heritage walls of the former Cinzano & Co warehouse, this house-like residence delivers a sense of space, privacy and community that's incredibly rare to find in this fashionable pocket of Alexandria. Reminiscent of an artist's loft in downtown Tribeca, this is inner city living on an epic scale with a sleek fusion of authentic industrial features and contemporary style that creates an inspiring home in which to live, work and play. Spread over two levels and wrapped in huge warehouse windows, the five-bedroom warehouse conversion is on the ground floor of the landmark Europa Apartments with secure level access, a private entertainer's deck and no common walls adding to its house-like feel. A dramatic gallery style living space serves as the social heart of the home while the mezzanine level is ideal as a home office and double-height ceilings bring the wow factor. With local institutions including Sonoma and Bourke Street Bakery just down the street, this dynamic neighbourhood south of the Green Square town centre is 750m to The Cannery's foodie hub and 550m to child-friendly Turruwul Park.

- House-like garden warehouse apartment, secure level access

description:
'The Woods' is an elegant 10 year old family home tucked away in one of Murrumbateman's most established and popular areas, the Woods Close just 30 minutes from Canberra CBD.

This large modern family home on a 9.3 acre block has all the features of country living including a dressage arena, serious shedding with vehicular access, five spacious bedrooms, two bathrooms, media room and separate office.

With established trees, immaculate gardens, manicured lawns and a swimming pool this property provides a wonderful opportunity for a relaxing and private country lifestyle all whilst lending itself to entertaining on summer nights.

The master bedroom is situated in it's own wing, separated from the other four bedrooms by a tiled open plan kitchen, dining and family room.

This 217m2 family friendly home has a media room and a private rumpus / family room.
Built with family in mind, the tidy and modern kitchen sits in the heart of the home overlooking the living and dining rooms flowing out to the large resort-style pool area.

With a separate office, just 50 metres from the main house, 'The Woods' offers the owner the perfect balance between country living and working from home options.

It includes two large paddocks at the front of the property, one with a dam, five smaller paddocks and four day yards, all electric fenced with automated water systems to most.

The property offers a two car garage to the residence, a five bay shed with vehicular access and two large additional sheds providing ample room and with a variety of options with how to use the space.

description:
"Dunollie" is a hidden oasis conveniently located on the outskirts of Murrumbateman.

This 30 acre property will captivate you with its private park-like atmosphere, expansive lawns, tranquil pool setting with flourishing views over the vineyard. All of this with the best cool climate Wineries at your doorstep.

One of the many significant features of this property is the homestead which has the charm of a traditional estate. Double brick residence, circa early 1900s, has been sympathetically restored and the extension complements the original features with high ceilings and views that form perfect pictures from each window.

The master bedroom has stunning views through sash windows over the vineyard and gardens, original open fireplace with marble mantle, entry to the sunroom and ensuite. Bedroom two and three, generous rooms with sash windows, bedroom three with open fireplace. The study makes working from home easy and can also be converted to a guest bedroom.

Combined family living with the dining and lounge. Brick feature walls, combustion wood heating, picture perfect views over the lawns and access to the BBQ area and inground pool. Functional kitchen with all the country living charms centrally located with butler's pantry polished boards and dual cooking facilities. Plenty of natural light and easy flow floor plan makes this a perfect family home. Spacious family bathroom with separate bath, shower and wc, master ensuite with shower, wc.

This region is best known for its cool climate wines and this property has established merlot and white table grape vines with watering system, orchid trees with apples, plums, fig, quince, pears, blood plum, mulberry, winter and summer raspberries, almond and walnut, established olive grove to name a few.

If you are the equine enthusiast, you will love the Olympic 60 x 20 all-weather arena, stables, storage/tack room, open bay parking, farm shed with timber floors and beams, let your imagination run free with this one - great entertainment space! Double carport of the main residence with storage cupboards all of these have power connected. Each of the eight paddocks have troughs automatically fed from the bore or freshwater tanks.

Be the new proud owner of this welcoming homestead with beautiful grounds and productive pastures all within easy proximity to the Barton highway, Canberra, Murrumbateman and Yass.
Inspections are a must please contact me today to arrange a viewing.

Features you will love:
*Double brick homestead with iron roof
*Inground pool registered
*Three bedrooms, Master with ensuite, study
*Family bathroom
*Kitchen with dual combustion or electric stove facilities, butlers pantry, dishwasher, breakfast bar, access to sun room,
*Dining room with views
*Family lounge with combustion heater and access to outdoor living
*Paved BBQ area
*Pergola with muscat grape vines
*Double carport with storage
*Stables with tack/storage room, double open bay parking, power
*Original Farm Shed with timber floors and beams, power
*60x20 all weather arena - metal base foundation and sand, cambered
*Bore with 20,000 lt storage tank plus dam, water to 8 paddocks
*Concrete water tank 20,000lt, further 2 tanks with 30,000lt combined
*Orchid trees - Some trees over 80 years old
*Vineyard - Merlot, table grapes, water system,

*Location: 8.9 km to Murrumbateman, 46.7 km to Canberra CBD, 17.8 km to Yass, 282 km to Sydney
*all distances are approximate only

Construction Double brick with iron roof
Land 12.62h

description:
A remarkable view has a way of reminding us of just how special this part of the world really is!

Standing high amid the Northern facing mountain range of the Korora Basin, 111 Bruxner Park Road offers you some of the most spectacular ocean, island and mountain views this precious stretch of coastline has to offer.

This small acreage property includes the original, partially renovated, 3 bedroom farmhouse that offers you a comfortable home to live in or can possibly become a second dwelling for the property (STCA), after you build your new forever home on the more elevated portion of the land.

A suggested building envelope (STCA) has been identified to make the most of the available views, presenting a fantastic opportunity for a discerning buyer and architect to create a stunning piece of modern real estate.

Surrounded by some of the most prestigious homes on the Mid North Coast, this elevated location allows you to whale watch from your living room as they migrate along the coast and marvel at the stunning electrical storms that dance over the ocean of a night-time.

You will never grow tired of watching the water animation created as the ocean waves strike the islands and rock formations. As you can imagine the sunrises over the ocean are often breathtaking and gazing at the sunsets over the Korora Basin ridgeline are a great way to end a relaxing day.

The property has a beautiful stand of Australian Iron Bark, Bloodwood, Strangler Fig, Grey gums, and Yellow Bean rainforest trees on the Southeast corner of the property offering both protection and filtered views back towards Coffs Harbour Marina.

In summer, you will enjoy the north-easterly breezes that provide fantastic natural cooling, while the North facing aspect ensures you have plenty of natural sunlight and winter sun.

A substantial concreted, private access road services the property from Bruxner Park Road and is also the right of carriageway access for the other 3 properties in the subdivision. Underground power is available to the site in the form of a new substation.

The existing, adjoining homes in the subdivision are architecturally designed homes of grand proportion ensuring any capital investment you undertake in your newly constructed home will be supported by these magnificent residences.

The current house consists of three bedrooms, one bathroom and offers parking by way of an attached carport. You experience ocean and island views from most rooms within, while the updates internally offer a great sense of warmth and comfort to the home.

Moving outside there is an outdoor deck and detached covered terrace for entertaining. The perfect space to relax and soak in the views while you sip your morning coffee.

This land has been long held within one family since 1969, a prime example of how opportunities like this seldom come available. The last remaining lot can now be yours and allows you the potential to design your very own dream home with astonishing coastal views.

Features:

- Incredible outlook across the Coffs Coastline which includes ocean, Solitary Island, and mountain views.
- 4 minutes' drive to Diggers Beach, a popular patrolled beach for swimming and surfing.
- 3 minutes' drive to the proposed new acting studios at Pacific Bay Resort.
- 5 minutes' drive to Park Beach Plaza Shopping Centre.
- 8 minutes' drive to Coffs Harbour CBD.
- 14 minutes' drive to airport with direct flights to Sydney and Melbourne.

description:
Nestled on a spacious 5.4acre parcel of land is this storybook custom designed family home, enjoying some of the most breathtaking views across the valley, Paterson River & distant mountain ranges. Having only been constructed 3.5 years ago this home was architecturally designed to take in the picturesque views, northern aspect & create the feeling of being worlds away, while only minutes from town. Enjoy being minutes from the Paterson River & local township offering pubs, restaurants, schools, grocers, cafes, train station, golf course & everything you could possibly need all at your fingertips. You are also only 20mins to Maitland CBD & 50mins to Newcastle CBD.

Coming down your country road surrounded by endless acres of farmland & space you will arrive at the fully concrete driveway leading you to the home. There is even parking at the start of the driveway for caravans & boats if desired. Continuing up your driveway there is plenty of open yard space for the kids & pets to play while all enjoying the amazing views on offer. Your driveway even has a roundabout at the end wide enough for 2 cars to pass each other & plenty of space for parking

Once at the home its grand stature will make you feel right at home as you enter through your patio to reveal soaring high ceilings, beautiful timber floors, premium lighting, the highest level of quality & the most amazing of views through a wall of glass windows & doors. Architecturally designed around the view you step down from your main hallway to a huge open plan living, dining & kitchen. Here you will find all the space you have dreamed of along with a combustion fireplace & reverse cycle a/c for year-round comfort. Your kitchen is ready for the biggest of gatherings showcasing 40mm stone benchtops, premium cabinetry, 900mm gas cooktop & oven, butlers pantry & so much more. The whole living, dining & kitchen opens through multiple glass sliding doors to a front balcony where you can spend hours entertaining while enjoying the breezes over the valley & picturesque views.
Located in a separate wing from the living are 3 king-size spare bedrooms each with a ceiling fan & 2 with built-in robes. These rooms share a luxury main bathroom with a frameless glass shower, freestanding bath & luxury inclusions. In addition to all of this, a timber staircase will lead you to the top of the home where a stunning master retreat awaits. Nestled in the clouds your master bedroom enjoys some of the most amazing views along with walk-in robe, luxury ensuite & a private balcony to enjoy a glass of wine while you watch the sunset across the valley.

This lovely home also offers a huge amount of under house storage, great bushwalks, unbroken valley views & plenty of space for the kids & pets to play. Certainly, a once in a lifetime opportunity, don't let this be the one that got away! Contact your team at Clarke & Co today for your next inspection.

description:
If you're looking for something unique, a home that is not identical to all the others in the suburb, then you'll be immediately drawn to this invitingly different home. The steeply pitched roofline evokes the character of a European ski chalet, soaring ceilings internally with exposed timber beams, along with an open, split-level design that creates a tremendous sense of space and light. The main living area features a dramatic staircase, elegant lighting, in floor heating plus a large combustion fire, and flows effortlessly outwards to the in-ground pool and entertaining spaces.

The modern kitchen boasts separate dining with access onto the remainder of the fully enclosed grassed yard, meaning you'll never be short of places to entertain and let the children and pets play. The bedrooms offer excellent privacy and separation, with the main on the ground floor which allows for mostly single level living should you so desire, and the remaining bedrooms positioned upstairs with a loft like feel.

Ideally positioned in a quiet, tree lined street, you'd be forgiven for forgetting you are just a few minutes walk to Fagan's Park, the waterfront reserve cycleway and popular Fare Cravin café. Also just a couple of minutes drive to Point Clare train station, shopping, primary school and eateries. In the other direction you'll find the newly being renovated West Gosford Shopping Centre just a moments drive, and a few minutes more and you'll be on the M1 motorway and in Sydney's North Shore in under an hour.

Ideal for those who dare to be different, but who still appreciate a well designed, functional and most importantly well located family home.

description:
MODERN, STYLISH AND SPACIOUS!

Low-maintenance yet stylish living is ready and waiting for the new owners of this two-storey semi detached home, perfectly positioned close to everything you could ever need. Alternatively, buyers on the hunt for the ultimate set-and-forget investment will adore this must-see abode that's sure to attract a wide range of eager tenants. The current tenants are paying $580 per week.

From the entry foyer, you are drawn through to the open-plan kitchen, dining and living room complete with a study nook and direct access to the covered alfresco. Chic 900mm stainless-steel appliances, a centre island and a walk-in pantry will delight the avid foodie plus there's ducted air-conditioning throughout, a main-floor laundry and a powder room for convenience.

There are four spacious bedrooms, including one on the ground level and three that are set on the first floor. The master has a dressing area, a built-in robe and an ensuite while all the secondary bedrooms have built-in robes.

A well-appointed main bathroom is set just off bedrooms two and three plus there's an open first-floor family room that's ideal for use as a rumpus or a second living zone. Completing the list of features is a double garage, with internal access, and an easy-care backyard that's fully fenced for privacy.

For families, Xavier College, Jordan Springs Public School and Corpus Christi Catholic Primary School are all nearby as are parks and playgrounds. The Jordan Springs Shopping Centre is conveniently located at your fingertips and you're just a short drive from the centre of Penrith and Kingswood with a long list of amenities on hand. A truly fantastic opportunity!

description:
Reward yourself with an exceptionally renovated residence that shines with warmth and contemporary charm. Perched at the heart of a sizable 1000m2 level allotment, all the hard work has been done for you in this spacious home. Light and airy throughout, you'll love the modern kitchen with its sleek finishes and style, with a meals area adjacent. Sunshine cascades into the living area where dual windows invite in views of the outdoors, plus a woodfire keeps it cosy in cooler months.

Three bedrooms are well proportioned plus you'll love the boldly on-trend bathroom. Beautifully presented, it's the perfect place to soak away any stress with a deep bath. Internal access from the single garage to the house is an added bonus as is the huge laundry.

Outdoors, a patio wraps itself around the home, with an entertaining area offering convenient, direct access to kitchen. There's a secluded feel to these sprawling gardens too, with a pine tree grove ideal for shady picnics at home or relaxing with a good book.

Centrally located, it's just five minutes to downtown Uralla, close to transport and walking distance to Uralla Central School. Don't let this chance to own a renovated home pass you by – arrange your inspection today.

description:
This modern three-bedroom abode is an ideal property to add to your investment portfolio or to enjoy yourself as a wonderful family home. Complete with a stylish interior, a functional floorplan, outdoor entertaining spaces and the potential to earn $400 a week, this is an opportunity you won’t want to miss.

The lucky new owners are sure to adore the open-plan kitchen, living and dining areas that connect seamlessly to the outdoor patio and backyard. Crisp white walls and easy-care tile floors frame the space while avid chefs will be greeted by on-trend cabinetry, a suite of stainless steel appliances and sweeping benchtops in the kitchen. At the front of the home, a separate lounge room is an ideal place to wind down at the end of a long day with your favourite movie or a good book.

Plush carpet is on show in the three bedrooms which all include built-in robes and are just steps from the main bathroom. The master bedroom also features an ensuite for ultimate peace and privacy.

Outside, a low-maintenance garden means you’ll spend more time doing what you love while eager entertainers will relish hosting Sunday barbeques with friends. Among this long list of features is evaporative air-conditioning throughout, gas hot water and a single garage complete with a roller door.

An ideal investment, this property is currently leased with a tenant in place until February 15th 2022. Enjoy returns of $400 per week or choose to keep the home for yourself once the lease expires.

Located within the Dubbo West Public School district, a six-minute walk from Macquarie Anglican Grammar School and only a short drive from Delroy Park Shopping Centre, you’ll have everything you need close by.

description:
Kristie Trouchet-Nilsson and Johan Nilsson present on behalf of Hartley Realty Lifestyle Properties 34 Doctors Gap Road, Lithgow. Please be in touch for more information.
Nestled in a secluded valley, close to town, with access to bushland for a small farm - this is what you have been waiting for.

34 Doctors Gap Road, Lithgow is an entirely original, weatherboard cottage in the bush - it is the renovator's dream!

Tucked away, sitting on the doorstep of Lithgow, lies this secluded, unique lifestyle opportunity you've been eagerly awaiting. Offering a three-bedroom weatherboard cottage, this is your entry-level chance to live a rural lifestyle yet still neighbouring the Blue Mountains, Lithgow & surrounds.

This home will speak volumes to first homeowners, property flippers, or investors.

The cottage is nicely sized and bestows views over the naturally vibrant bushland. Internally, the home is configured as three bedrooms one bathroom. Externally, there is ample space for cars, caravans, trailers, or boats! This cottage is ready to begin its next chapter.

It is still in its original condition and ideally seeking someone to come in and restore it to its former glory. This is an unusual opportunity. You're buying one share of 22 shares and 4 shares of 88 in the total land as tenant in common. This effectively gives you the house and shares but you do not own the land the house sits on or the 4 acres as such.

Creativity, sustainability and beauty are the cornerstones of this potential-packed masterpiece. Your options seem limitless. With room to extend or renovate, this home is adaptable yet timeless and ladened with potential.

Ample water is provided from the rainwater tank, two natural springs and creeks at both the front and back of the house. Meaning hobby farms would excel.

Four stunning acres (approx.) of established hobby-farming land, with an abundance on offer, is share-farmed with the local community for added convenience & less hassle, with all-weather vehicle access.

Settled on the edge of the Lithgow shopping strip, its location is natural, unique and instantly injects character into your lifestyle. This ideal hobby farm has a great mix of cleared space and natural bushland.

Proximity to quality local schooling, shops and public transport means the cottage is ideal to live in now, flip or renovate to rent and will build value as the community grows.

- Only minutes from Lithgow
- Entry-level purchase price
- Your dream hobby farm with access to approx 4 community acres
- Three-bedroom weatherboard cottage
- Very peaceful
- Connected to mains power and a suitable septic system
- Reverse cycle air-conditioning
- Established gardens with a mix of bush and cleared land
- Great potential
- Rainwater tank
- 2 creeks and spring water (2 springs on the property)
- Renovator's dream
- Shedding suitable for many endeavours
– Lovely rural outlook & great lifestyle property

The property has been well-maintained until recently & beautifully established during its much-loved life.

An outstanding opportunity with superb bush outlooks, ample water, and stunning sunsets are just a few of the spectacular features of this delightful country property that first-time buyers, renovators and investors with an eye for value won't want to miss.

Contact Kristie Trouchet-Nilsson on 0400 203 383 immediately to avoid disappointment.

description:
ARCHITECTURAL ARTISTRY HAS ARRIVED IN KINGSCLIFF - PINNACLE OF LUXURIOUS PERFECTION
OH MY GOSH - WOW!

Inspired by the brilliance of Brazilian Architect, Marcio Kogan (MK27), Jayson Pate has designed a residence of unrivalled quality & construction in this region.

The home was awarded the MASTER BUILDERS NORTHERN NSW AWARD in 2019.

Welcome to "12 Cylinders", designed to adopt a modern brutalist construction into a functional & simplistic home.

The design brief was to create an open, light filled family home, while maintaining privacy on a premium corner site. The aim was to generate an organic and striking figure that utilises materials in their essence, without manipulation.

The character of the residence is generated by the inclusion of an off-form concrete body that dramatically cantilevers over the underlying living spaces. Concrete is utilised throughout the upper volume, creating the illusion of floating atop the delicate glass form below.

A TROPHY RESIDENCE IN EXCLUSIVE CYLINDERS DRIVE, KINGSCLIFF

Walk across to beautiful Kingscliff Beach or to the local cafes, shops & restaurants of Salt Village nearby.
Boasting an enviable northern corner aspect, this dual level solidly constructed home has commercial grade finishes & bespoke detailing.

No expense has been spared in its unique architecture, custom built design & timeless quality finishes.
With dual street access, the pedestrian entry is secured by electronic card & keyless access to ensure your privacy & security.

The WOW FACTOR is evident from entry & continues throughout the entire home.

Dramatic voids, 10ft ceilings, an air-conditioned wine cellar, cold goods room, gymnasium, mosaic tiled steam room, 3 car garage & Villeroy & Bosh bathroom finishes are just some of the many features that stand this incredible home well above other properties in this area. Quality in both construction & appointments of this proportion are rare in residential real estate.

UNIQUE ARCHITECTURE, FORWARD AESTHETICS & TIMELESS QUALITY INCLUSIONS

The state-of-the-art kitchen & butler's pantry are absolutely stunning !! A temperature controlled cold room & air-conditioned glass wine cellar adjoin the kitchen to service all your entertaining needs in style.
Floor to ceiling custom cabinetry, Smeg Dolce Stil Novo appliances, integrated Liebherr fridge/freezer, 3 dish drawers, double pyrolytic ovens, zip tap with boiling, sparkling & chilled water are set around the huge central island bench, where family & many friends can gather in casual comfort.

Words understate the WOW FACTOR this home exudes, so I invite you to view the professional photos available to discerning buyers.

Feature stone walls enhance the privacy of the internal living spaces & 16 metres of north facing, cavity sliding, commercial grade glass doors connect seamlessly to the outdoor alfresco zones. A two-way gas fireplace creates a warm & inviting ambiance to the lounge & dining rooms, where you can sip on a glass of red during those chilly winter nights.

The light filled living areas are enhanced by the 16-metre linear pool that elongates the northern landscape. A 20-year-old South African Aloe tree stands proudly in the corner of the generous yard area.
Entertain in casual elegance from your full 316 marine grade stainless steel outdoor kitchen with Beefeater flatline BBQ & Scope icemaker.

A separate built-in stone topped bar is just the spot for your afternoon cocktails by the pool !!

The upper level is linked by concrete stairs, topped with engineered timber & crowned by soaring voided ceilings. A 2nd living or library zone provides great separated space away from the main living downstairs.

A LIFESTYLE OF ENVIABLE ELEGANCE & GRANDEUR AWAITS YOUR INSPECTION

CONTRACT NICK WITHERIFF on 0405 618 477 TO ARRANGE YOUR PRIVATE VIEWING OPPORTUNITY.

PROPERTY FEATURES:
- 4 designer bedroom suites with keyless access
- 4 ultra-modern bathrooms
- Additional powder room downstairs
- 5th bedroom/Gymnasium with ensuite option
- Fully mosaic tiled steam room with Mr Steam iPad temperature control
- 2nd living room/library upstairs
- Huge laundry with laundry chute & access to drying yard
- Cold goods storage room (temperature controlled)
- Air-conditioned glass wine cellar
- 10ft ceilings & glass doors downstairs
- 9ft ceilings & glass upstairs
- Sonos sound system with 8 amplifiers & roof speakers
- Floor to ceiling cabinetry throughout
- Ducted, zoned air conditioning (2 separate systems)
- Escea (NZ) dual sided gas fireplace (remote & phone app controlled)
- Pandomo like concrete flooring downstairs & externally
- Engineered timber flooring upstairs
- 3-metre-wide cantilevered alfresco entertaining zone
- Stone topped poolside bar
- Outdoor 316 stainless steel kitchen
- 16-metre-long swimming pool
- Astro turf to yard areas
- Cobblestone entry & driveway
- Solar system - 15kwt
- Fully fenced yard with mature landscaping
- 3 car garage with extra storage & epoxy flooring
- 720m2 beachside corner block
- Option to buy fully furnished (POA)

5 MINUTES TO TWEED VALLEY HOSPITAL (under construction)
15 MINUTES TO GOLD COAST AIRPORT
30 MINUTES TO BYRON BAY
CLOSE TO BEACH, SHOPS, CAFES, RESTAURANTS, SALT VILLAGE, CHILD CARE, MEDICAL & KINGSCLIFF TOWNSHIP
